= May 15 incident 

On May 15, 1932, Japanese far-right naval officers, aided by army cadets, and right-wing civilian elements (including Shūmei Ōkawa, Mitsuru Tōyama, and Kōzaburō Tachibana) staged their attempt to complete what had been started in the League of Blood Incident. Prime Minister Inukai Tsuyoshi was shot by eleven young naval officers, many of whom had only recently turned twenty years of age, in the prime minister's residence.


- @condemn: Condemn the assasination publicly.
- @leave_it_to_japan: Leave the incident in Japan.
- @do_own_shit: Why didn't we think of this.


@condemn
subtitle: We will condemn the assasination
